            "title": "Adoption from Care : International Perspectives on Children\u2019s Rights, Family Preservation and State Intervention",
            "abstract": "\"EPDF and EPUB available Open Access under CC-BY-NC-ND.  This book explores how children\u2019s rights are practised and weighed against parents\u2019 rights in a range of countries, and examines how governments and legal and welfare professionals balance those rights in the challenging circumstances following the decision that children cannot grow up in their parents\u2019 care.  Looking at adoption from care in Europe and the United States, it provides in-depth analysis of concepts of family, contact, the child\u2019s best interest principle and human rights in adoption from care across these different socio-political and legal contexts.  Taking an international comparative approach to these issues, this book provides best practice evidence on adoption processes and shares learning across country boundaries to help improve outcomes for all adopted children.\"",
